Description: Fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration. The rear shows flat area with the impression of wood. The front side is flat and shows an impression of an oval seal with the lower part preserved. The motif is a bit blurred, not cut very sharply. Visible is a circumferential line, remains of what could be nfr at the left, only small parts of the sign left of it and underneath a flat elongated sign like a nb.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Amara West (Nubia), E14.7 temple magazine
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
